00:31:27.140 --> 00:31:29.330 align:middle line:10%
unsanitary, unhealthy.

00:31:29.330 --> 00:31:32.270 align:middle line:84%
But if they put some antibiotic
in their food every day,

00:31:32.270 --> 00:31:37.352 align:middle line:84%
they felt that they were
stopping the animal illness.

00:31:37.352 --> 00:31:38.810 align:middle line:84%
And that's about
the same as trying

00:31:38.810 --> 00:31:41.180 align:middle line:84%
to sprinkle antibiotic
on your children's cereal

00:31:41.180 --> 00:31:42.080 align:middle line:90%
every morning.

00:31:42.080 --> 00:31:43.460 align:middle line:90%
It makes about as much sense.

00:31:43.460 --> 00:31:56.860 align:middle line:90%


00:31:56.860 --> 00:32:01.330 align:middle line:84%
>> Today, agriculture is going
far beyond nature to produce

00:32:01.330 --> 00:32:05.440 align:middle line:84%
new miracles for an even
better, more abundant life.

00:32:05.440 --> 00:32:07.615 align:middle line:90%


00:32:07.615 --> 00:32:10.190 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, we produce 9 billion
food animals in the United

00:32:10.190 --> 00:32:10.990 align:middle line:90%
States every year.

00:32:10.990 --> 00:32:13.510 align:middle line:84%
So those are animals
that we raise for meat.

00:32:13.510 --> 00:32:16.482 align:middle line:10%
And those 9 billion
animals-- most of those

00:32:16.482 --> 00:32:18.190 align:middle line:10%
are raised in Concentrated
Animal Feeding

00:32:18.190 --> 00:32:22.745 align:middle line:10%
Operations, or CAFOs, and given
